channel.title: Help with wireless network
channel.description:
there is this guy around our house who has wireless internet named "default" (its unprotected)
as you would expect, i use his internet instead of mine.
i have downloaded a lot of stuff.
you know some of those services who charge extra per megabyte for going over download limit? i wonder if he has one of those plans.
i would feel really bad if i get him a huge bill.
so i was wondering is there anyway for me to know his download limit or trace the wireless connection to his house so i can ask him? or to find out what his download limit or plan is.
these are the details i have so far: ip: 122.108.18.145 (OPTUS INTERNET - RETAIL)
i traced the ip and got: c122-108-18-145.eburwd9.vic.optusnet.com.au
any clue? ps.im in melbourne Australia.
